---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - Justin Doone"
  description="Marketing manager at Evolve ETFs. Started in hospitality marketing in Hong Kong; built through Greybrook Realty Partners and Clifton Blake before landing in ETFs."
>
  <!-- HERO (dark) -->
  <section class="dark-section relative pt-24 md:pt-36 pb-12 md:pb-16">
    <div class="hero-orb hero-orb-a" style="top: -10%; right: -15%;"></div>
    <div
      class="hero-orb hero-orb-b"
      style="bottom: -25%; left: 0%; opacity: 0.25; background: radial-gradient(circle, var(--color-accent-cool), transparent 60%);"
    ></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12">
      <img
        src="/images/profile.jpg"
        alt="Justin Doone"
        width="200"
        height="200"
        class="hero-line w-36 h-36 md:w-44 md:h-44 rounded-full object-cover mb-10 ring-1 ring-on-dark-mute"
        data-line="0"
      />
      <p class="hero-line eyebrow mb-8" data-line="0">About</p>
      <h1
        class="hero-line heading-display text-5xl md:text-7xl mb-10 leading-[0.95]"
        data-line="1"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark);"
      >
        The job has gotten more <em style="color: var(--color-accent); font-style: italic;">technical</em> every year I've done it.
      </h1>
      <p
        class="hero-line text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6"
        data-line="2"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark);"
      >
        I came up in hospitality marketing in Hong Kong, working at a boutique hotel through a rebrand and the staycation pivot that followed it. Real estate marketing at Greybrook and Clifton Blake came next. ETF marketing at Evolve, where I run digital end-to-end for a 44-fund lineup, is the most technical version of the work I've done so far.
      </p>
      <p
        class="hero-line text-lg leading-relaxed"
        data-line="3"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark-soft);"
      >
        Each step has required more analytics and more in-house tooling than the last.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW I WORK (dark, continued) -->
  <section class="dark-section relative py-16 md:py-20" data-reveal>
    <div
      class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 rule-top pt-16"
    >
      <p class="eyebrow mb-8">How I work</p>
      <div
        class="space-y-8 leading-relaxed text-lg"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark-soft);"
      >
        <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
          I do the analytics part myself. SQL, dashboards, the meeting where someone argues their channel deserves more credit. Used to be a separate function in most marketing teams; on a lean one it's the same person. The strategy is sharper when I can see what the data is doing, and harder to lie to.
        </p>
        <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
          I work mostly in financial services and other regulated rooms. That's trained me to write to the compliance line, not over it. The difference between launching this quarter and launching next is usually one careful first draft.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA (dark) -->
  <section class="dark-section relative py-24 md:py-32" data-reveal>
    <div class="hero-orb" style="top: 0%; right: -10%; opacity: 0.3;"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-6">Get in touch</p>
      <h2
        class="heading-display text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-8"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark);"
      >
        Tell me what you're trying to ship.
      </h2>
      <a
        href="mailto:justindoone@gmail.com"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent text-paper px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-accent-warm transition-colors"
      >
        justindoone@gmail.com
        <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
